{"key":"post-6827731","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6827731</id>\n<content>Misting with a cheap mister that spits out large droplets will bruise the fruits.  You need to mist with a high quality mister that produces a very fine, fog like mist.  Even then, mist upwards into the air, so that the fine foggy mist simply settles gently onto the cakes.  Always up the air exchange after misting so the fruits don't sit there wet.  Wet fruits often abort.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>6827995</next>\n<prev>6827661</prev>\n<first>6827661</first>\n<last>6828693</last>\n<when>1177444884</when>\n<utime>04/24/07 11:01 PM</utime>\n</post>"}